            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "With more than one `%w`, `fmt.Errorf` returns an error whose `Unwrap() []error` returns multiple wrapped errors rather than a single `Unwrap() error`.\n\nA few source-level details from `fmt/errors.go`:\n- if the same argument is wrapped more than once, it only appears once in the returned `[]error`\n- with positional formatting, the wrapped errors are ordered by argument index before duplicates are removed\n- the rendered error message still includes every formatted `%w` occurrence in the normal output text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
